      "date": "2015-11-19 22:55:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nPatch itself looks good, but if this was broken by some previous patch and we didn't notice it then it means we don't have a test for \"lctl list_param -R\" to verify it is working correctly. \n\nThis is a bit tricky because the exact names of files in /proc change between versions, but it seems we do need a test case to ensure it continue to work, since there are more patches coming in this area. Please think of a way to test this. \n\nOne way is to just count the number of entries in some subtree, so that it only depends on $OSTCOUNT and that we already know, like:\n\n    local NUM=$(lctl list_param -R \"osc.*\" \"mdc.*\" | grep -c max_rpcs_in_flight)\n    [[ $NUM == $((OSTCOUNT + MDSCOUNT)) ]] || error \"...\"",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "f4f1d5dee571fe5bd6a6d0310fcdc8f4b551ac68",
